        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         When I went and camped my HS key and was hoping to get the staff, what I did once down there, was to keep IVU up, and sit behind/beside the church.  Just to the left of the walkway down.  Right next to the large open cylinder thing with skellies in it.  That way you are facing the side/rear of the church.  (sounds kind off confusing but you'll know what I mean when you're down there).  Then I would just kill the ph/Xalgoz the same way each time.  IVU, go to the front of the church and target the PH/Xalgoz.  Go back to your semi-safe spot, and I would pull him with the 39 undead slow.  He will path to you around the back of the cylinder, this gives you time to wait a couple secs and then start casting Banish undead.  If you time it right, then he will come around the back corner area and stop to cast on you, your nuke will land on him, rinse and repeat.  With the undead slow on him, he is a chump and you should not have any adds, if you do you can ST them and it's a piece of cake.</P><P>-Morgath</P><P>"we feel sorry for those of you that don't drink, because when you get up in the morning, that's as good as you'll feel for the rest of the day"<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
